    <h2>Browser updates</h2> 
<p>Updates for first-party browsers such as Microsoft Edge, Internet Explorer and Apple Safari are often included in OS updates. If your OS is configured to update automatically, so too will your first-party browser update automatically.</p> 
<p>Third-party browsers such as&nbsp;<a href="http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/new/?from=getfirefox">Mozilla Firefox<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.google.com/intl/en/chrome/browser/">Google Chrome<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="http://www.opera.com/computer/windows">Opera<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>can also be configured to download and install updates automatically. You can also manually download updated versions on their respective websites.</p>
    





